## 4. Debug Output

**Micro-controller** scripts may satisfy this section with aggregate init and registration lines. **Full controllers** should use the fuller patterns below.

### 4.1 `debugPrint` pattern

```lua
local const = {
    roomName    = "Room 101",
    debug       = true,
    clearString = "-- Select --"
}

local function debugPrint(str)
    if const.debug then print("[" .. const.roomName .. "] " .. str) end
end
```

### 4.2 What to log

| ✅ Always log | ❌ Never log |
|---|---|
| Initialization phases (`=== Started ===`, `=== Complete ===`) | Redundant "already at state" on every poll |
| Component discovery (what found, counts) | Internal utilities called thousands of times |
| Event handler registration (type + count) | Timer tick operations where nothing changed |
| Every routing/switching operation | |
| State changes (before → after) | |
| Safety blocks / errors | |
| Source attribution on all operations | |

### 4.3 Required patterns (full controller)

```lua
-- In init()
debugPrint("=== Initialization Started ===")
debugPrint("Configuration: const.roomName=" .. const.roomName .. ", debugging=" .. tostring(const.debug))
-- ... setup ...
debugPrint("=== Initialization Complete ===")
debugPrint("Ready for operation")

-- Source attribution on all state changes
debugPrint("Wall 3 (SalonB/SalonC) → CLOSED (Source: Wall Button)")
debugPrint("Room SalonD → ON (Source: Combination Selector)")
debugPrint("Audio routing: SalonD → Input 3 (Source: Room Combiner)")

-- Count things at registration time
debugPrint("Registered " .. wallCount .. " wall button handlers")
debugPrint("Registered " .. rcCount   .. " room control handlers")

-- Before/after for significant state transitions
debugPrint("Room component 3 (SalonA): 'compRoomA_old' → 'compRoomA_new'")
```

