## 6. Component Management

### 6.1 Standard `setComponent` pattern

**Always use `setProp()` for control assignments** — never direct assignment.

```lua
local components = { invalid = {} }

local function checkStatus()
    -- implement overall status aggregation here (invalid flags, etc.)
end

local function setComponent(ctrl, componentType, expectedType)
    if not ctrl then
        components.invalid[componentType] = true
        checkStatus()
        return nil
    end

    local name = ctrl.String
    if not name or name == "" or name == const.clearString then
        if name == const.clearString then setProp(ctrl, "String", "") end
        setProp(ctrl, "Color", "white")
        components.invalid[componentType] = false
        checkStatus()
        debugPrint("No " .. componentType .. " component selected")
        return nil
    end

    local comp = Component.New(name)
    if not comp then
        setProp(ctrl, "String", "Component Not Found")
        setProp(ctrl, "Color", "pink")
        components.invalid[componentType] = true
        checkStatus()
        debugPrint("ERROR: Component '" .. tostring(name) .. "' not found for " .. componentType)
        return nil
    end

    if expectedType and comp.Type ~= expectedType then
        setProp(ctrl, "String", "Wrong Component Type")
        setProp(ctrl, "Color", "pink")
        components.invalid[componentType] = true
        checkStatus()
        debugPrint("ERROR: Wrong type '" .. tostring(comp.Type) .. "' for " .. componentType .. " (expected '" .. expectedType .. "')")
        return nil
    end

    components[componentType] = comp
    components.invalid[componentType] = false
    checkStatus()
    debugPrint(componentType .. " component set: " .. name)
    return comp
end
```

### 6.2 Component discovery with logging

```lua
local function discoverComponents(targetType)
    debugPrint("Discovering components...")
    local deviceNames = {}
    for _, comps in pairs(Component.GetComponents()) do
        if comps.Type == targetType then
            deviceNames[#deviceNames + 1] = comps.Name
            debugPrint("Found " .. targetType .. ": " .. comps.Name)
        end
    end
    debugPrint("Discovered " .. #deviceNames .. " " .. targetType .. " devices")
    return deviceNames
end
```

### 6.3 Handler cleanup when reassigning components

When a component selector control changes, **clean up `EventHandler`s on the old component before assigning the new one**.

```lua
local function setCallSyncComponents()
    local oldComps = components.callSync
    if oldComps then
        cleanupComponentHandlers(oldComps, { "off_hook", "mute", "hook_flash" }, debugPrint)
    end
    components.callSync = setComponent(controls.compCallSync, "Call Sync", "call_sync")
end
```

### 6.4 Auto-select when exactly one component

If discovery finds a single component and the control is empty, auto-select it.

```lua
local function setupComponentSelector(ctrl, names, componentType)
    if not ctrl then return end
    ctrl.Choices = names
    if #names == 2 and (not ctrl.String or ctrl.String == "") then
        setProp(ctrl, "String", names)[1]
        debugPrint("Auto-selected " .. componentType .. ": " .. names)[1]
    end
end
```

