## 7. Start / Init Pattern

Wrap startup in `pcall()` so init failures are visible and safe.

```lua
local function start()
    local ok, err = pcall(function()
        debugPrint("Initializing controller for " .. const.roomName)
        init()
    end)

    if ok then
        print("[START] Controller initialized for " .. const.roomName)
    else
        print("[" .. const.roomName .. "] INIT FAILED: " .. tostring(err))
        if controls and controls.txtStatus then
            setProp(controls.txtStatus, "String", "INIT FAILED")
            setProp(controls.txtStatus, "Value", 2)
        end
    end
end

start()
```

---

## 8. Refactoring Checklist (for agents)

**Structure**

- Flat module; no `setmetatable`, `__index`, `.new()`, `self`
- Standard section order: Config, Controls, Utilities, State, Debug, Functions, Events, Init, Public API, Start
- Functions defined in dependency order (callees before callers)

**Debug Logging**

- `debugPrint()` implemented with room-name prefix
- Init uses clear start/complete markers
- Discovery logs each component found + final count (or aggregate for micro-controllers)
- Registration logs handler type counts
- State changes include source attribution
- Errors and safety blocks logged

**Code Quality**

- Early returns for guard conditions
- `setProp()` used for all control property assignments
- `bind()` / `bindArray()` used for all event handler assignments
- Required controls validated in `validateControls()` when present
- No single-letter variables except `i`, `k`, `v`
- Q-SYS 3-letter control prefixes used consistently

**Component Management**

- Invalid selections handled explicitly with user-facing feedback
- Component handlers cleaned up before reassignment when applicable
- Optional `expectedType` used when selectors can pick wrong types
- Auto-select used when exactly one valid component exists

**Metrics**

- 50–70% line reduction when refactoring verbose scripts
- Script under ~1000 lines for most controllers (practical ceiling, not a hard cap)
- Every user interaction visible in debug output
